{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require gaming developers to make games adaptable for disabled users",
        "additional_details": "We are concerned that most gaming companies are slowly making their games less accessible to disabled users. We find this unfair and a barrier in the quality of disabled users lives. We think the gaming developers are cutting costs and phasing out the use of a gaming steering wheel which makes it difficult for those with conditions connected to hand/finger functionality unable to enjoy playing games.",
        "background": "Require gaming developers to make their games adaptable for disabled users. For example have racing games compatible with a gaming steering wheel for those with cerebral palsy or similar conditions.",
